                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">57 Mage here on Mal'Ganis;
<br />

<br />
I am an Arcane/Fire crit build spec, with 28 Arcane and 20 fire (going to be 23 fire).
<br />

<br />
For solo, if I'm single mob killing, I start at range (obviously), cast two fireballs (mob reaches me right when the second fires), followed by a fireblast and then an Arcane Missles salvo.  If the mob has a significant amount of HP remaining, do either fireblast, Arcane Missles, or if you're really desperate PoM a Pyroblast.  If the mob has a small amount of HP left, use scorch.
<br />

<br />
For PvP, it depends which class.  Generally, use Poly to start off (also, Polymorph will dismount someone who is mounted) to allow yourself time to get a fireball off, use fireblast whenever it is available, and blow your Presence of Mind when you want to finish off the player.  If you find yourself not knowing what to do, use scorch, or if the opponent is in melee range and you've already blown your Frost Nova, use Improved Arcane Explosion or Cone of Cold.  If a rogue (or any other class) stuns you with Kidney Shot or jumps you with Cheap Shot, blink.  PvP is all about timing for a mage; either timing the Frost Nova, or timing the Cone of Cold, or the blink, or timing the counterspell.
<br />

<br />
For groups (not raids, haven't raided yet), use polymorph just as you would mesmerize with an enchanter, keeping in mind you can only poly 1 mob at a time, and polymorph draws almost zero agro.  Remember also poly is not fixed duration.  In groups, damage-wise, I like to spam scorch.  I have incinerate and impact talents, which gives my scorch a good crit rate, as well as a chance to stun.  Also, it's a cheap way to keep your mana up in case you need to pour on the heat in a bad situation.  If your clearcasting pops from spamming scorch, use a more mana-intensive spell, like fireball.  If you are aggrod, hit frost nova and back away, let your tank regain agro.
<br />

<br />
Mages are a great and extremely versatile class.  In PvP, beware of priests and shamans especially.  
<br />

<br />
Perhaps it should be noted that I am horde.  If you want to make a horde mage, I suggest undead.  I have been saved by Will of the Forsaken so many times against priests and warlocks; I don't know what I'd do without it.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
