                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Im a Frost Mage (one of the few, actually) on our server at 60. Here is my Talent Spec:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Arcane Talents (17 points)
<br />
-----
<br />
Arcane Subtlety - 3/3 points
<br />
Reduces the threat generated by your offensive arcane spells by 40%.
<br />

<br />
Improved Arcane Missiles - 5/5 points
<br />
Gives you a 100% chance to avoid interruption caused by damage while channeling Arcane Missiles.
<br />

<br />
Arcane Concentration - 5/5 points
<br />
Gives you a 10% chance of entering a Clearcasting state after any damage spell hits a target. The Clearcasting state reduces the mana cost of your next damage spell by 100%.
<br />

<br />
Evocation - 1/1 point
<br />
While channeling this spell, your mana regeneration is active and increased by 1500%. Lasts 8 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Improved Arcane Explosion - 3/5 points
<br />
Reduces the casting time of your Arcane Explosion by 0.9 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Frost Talents (34 points)
<br />
-----
<br />
Permafrost - 5/5 points
<br />
Increases the duration of your chill effects by 3 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Improved Frost Nova - 2/2 points
<br />
Reduces the cooldown of your Frost Nova spell by 4 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Ice Shards - 5/5 points
<br />
Increases the critical strike damage bonus of your Frost spells by 100%.
<br />

<br />
Winter's Chill - 3/3 points
<br />
Increases the power of your chill effects by slowing the target's movement by an additional 10%.
<br />

<br />
Piercing Ice - 3/3 points
<br />
Increases the damage done by your frost spells by 6%.
<br />

<br />
Cold Snap - 1/1 point
<br />
When activated, this spell finishes the cooldown on all of your cold spells.
<br />

<br />
Improved Blizzard - 2/3 points
<br />
Adds a chill effect to your Blizzard spell. This effect lowers the target's movement speed to 50% of normal. Lasts 8.50 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Arctic Reach - 2/2 points
<br />
Increases the range of your Frostbolt spell and the radius of your Frost Nova and Cone of Cold spells by 20%.
<br />

<br />
Frost Channeling - 3/3 points
<br />
Reduces the mana cost of your frost spells by 15%.
<br />

<br />
Shatter - 3/5 points
<br />
Increases the critical strike chance of your frost spells against frozen targets by 30%.
<br />

<br />
Ice Block - 1/1 point
<br />
You become encased in a block of ice, protecting you from all physical attacks and spells for 10 seconds, but during that time you cannot attack, move, or cast spells.
<br />

<br />
Frostbite - 3/5 points
<br />
Gives your chill effects a 9% chance to freeze the target for 5 seconds.
<br />

<br />
Ice Barrier - 1/1 point
<br />
Instantly shields you, absorbing 455 damage. Lasts 1 minute. While the shield holds, spells will not be interrupted.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
For solo grouping, Ill use Ice Armor, and pull with Frost Bolt at maximum distance. Ill usually open with another Frost Bolt or two, and possibly a Fire Bolt (for the DoT). Mob is slowed by now from smacking my armor, so I fire off a Nova, Cone of Cold (for added snare) and repeat. If Im looking to pump out a lot of damage Ill throw Arcane Missles. These will drain my mana pool fast though, so I usem sparingly. I dont solo 'fast' as other classes due to the lack of Fire DPS but I get the job done.
<br />

<br />
For groups, Ill typically sniper mobs with Frost Bolt (if their solo) or if there are two either use Poly or Frost Bolt (depending on the mob). It really depends on where you fight and the NPCs you fight, but I find that with Frost I can keep the mobs snared indefinitely, rooted, and away from groupmates in sticky situations much better than if I were a Fire mage. Likewise, I notice less aggro (with greater DPS due to criticals and +DMGs) with Frost, so I can chain cast Frost Bolt to my hearts content. In areas with large amounts of AoE mobs (like the lil plants in Dire Maul), I use a long range Blizzard (due to snare, chill) to pull. When they get in close, their usually 3/4 dead and one quick IAE finishes the job.
<br />

<br />
In raids, I do fantastic with this Talent spec. I use the same Frost Bolt sniping tactics, as well as long range Blizzards, and Im still able to fire off quick IAEs (IF necessary). Now Im sure someone will point out the inherent flaw about Frost Mages having to spend all their points to get the full benefit of Frost, and that my setup is 'half-assed' but for what I do, and the situations I partake in, its an excellent option if your looking for an excellent defensive & offensive option. Mana isnt really an issue either, due to Evocation.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
