                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Never go fire and ice at once.  </span>
<br />

<br />
Arcane is a must; you will get laughed at if you are level 60 and don't have improved arcane explosion.  If you aren't going to go any further, definately get evocation too.  Only reason I'd ever get the +%mana talent is if you're going for arcane instability, and arcane power.
<br />

<br />
If you're going to go for improved flamestrike, do yourself a favor and get blast wave.
<br />

<br />
Also, Pyroblast isn't a great talent.  It costs 6 points, and especially at 60 isn't that great considering 80% of mobs in high end raids are immune to fire.  For grinding, I'd go with it because the faster fireball is very handy.
<br />

<br />
Ditch the point you put into arcane meditation, it doesn't stack with mage armor, making it worthless.  Put it into mana shield or dampen magic.
<br />

<br />
Currently I have the following build:
<br />

<br />
23 Fire
<br />
Impact 5
<br />
Ignite 5
<br />
Improved Fireblast 5
<br />
Incinerate 2
<br />
Flamethrowing 2
<br />
Burning Soul 1 (Had to put it somewhere, and improved scorch is awful)
<br />
Critical Mass 3
<br />

<br />
28 Arcane
<br />

<br />
Improved Arcane Missiles 5
<br />
Arcane Concentration 5
<br />
Improved AE 5
<br />
Evocation 1
<br />
Improved Counterspell 2
<br />
Improved Dampen Magic 2
<br />
Presence of Mind 1
<br />
Arcane Mind 4
<br />
Arcane Instability 3
<br />

<br />
Works extremely well in PvP, my spells have a huge chance to crit, and PoM allows me to seal the kill, or throw an instant poly and make myself scarce.  In instances, my scorch has a good crit rate, along with the additional crit damage from ignite.
<br />

<br />
My advice, go ice or fire.  Always get Improved AE.   Other than that, you can choose whether you want to crit more, or have a one-trick-pony type deal with arcane power or combustion.
<br />

<br />
Good luck,
<br />

<br />
Owin,  60 Mage, Mal'Ganis</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Burninater on Sun Apr 03, 2005 10:30 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
                        </tr>
