                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">Arcane is a must; you will get laughed at if you are level 60 and don't have improved arcane explosion</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I didnt get 100% Improved Arcane Explosion because I dont see how pressing the IWIN button is challenging. You CAN do AOES just as effective (if not BETTER) than with IAE if specced right. How? Simple. As Frost Im regularly pulling large groups of AoE mobs long range in Strath, using Improved Blizzard w/ chill effects. The snare & roots setup the mobs for other AOErs to launch their volley, long before the mobs reach our group. When they DO reach us, I Frost Nova, and finish off whatevers left (usually their at 1/4 life and or dead) with Arcane Explosion.
<br />

<br />
It typically depends on the guild, and who your with. You DONT need Improved Arcane Explosion to win high-end encounters that Ive seen, and with a well-balanced raid or group youll do just fine using Fire / Ice AoEs over a fully-specced Arcane Explosion.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
